It's an interesting comment on\nthe nostalgia for the market
as Indonesia reinterprets\nand reincorporates
her historical legacies.
Even if they were part colonial.
Official word has it that the\nmarket will be resurrected
by 2020, though\nthat's a long time
for these small-scale\nmerchants to wait.
And rumors persist that\nit is really a land grab.
For the plans of the\nrehabilitated market
and its intended use are\nvery hard to come by.
My interest in Karsten\ncontinued to grow as I traveled.
And I visited the Pasar\nRandusari and the Pasar
Jatingaleh and the Pasar\nCinde, all of which
deployed the big roof as a means\nto aggregate the small scale
